**Professional tax** is levied by state governments on employment income. It is deductible from gross salary income and also allowed as deduction under Section 16 of the Income Tax Act. Rates differ by state: Maharashtra charges up to ₹2,500/year; West Bengal, Karnataka, Tamil Nadu also levy PT. Some states like Delhi, Haryana, UP do not have professional tax.
